Figure 4.32 Sites of maximum intensity and radiation of murmurs and heart sounds
(a) Systolic murmurs:
AS = aortic stenosis;
MR = mitral regurgitation;
HCM = hypertrophic cardiomyopathy;
PS = pulmonary stenosis;
VSD = ventricular septal defect;
I = innocent.
(b) Diastolic murmurs and sounds:
AR = aortic regurgitation;
MS = mitral stenosis;
S3 = third heart sound;
PR = pulmonary regurgitation;
PDA = patent ductus arteriosus (continuous murmur).

Associated features

As already mentioned, the cause of a cardiac murmur can sometimes be
elicited by careful analysis of the peripheral signs.
Timing (Table 4.15)

Systolic murmurs (which occur during ventricular systole) may be
pansystolic, ejection systolic or late systolic.
